Streams-
Represent sequence of objects of specific type from source which support aggregate operations.
Never stores.
IO streams or collection
Aggregate operations-> map, filter, map, reduce
stream gives stream mostly input-> process-> stream (collect //terminal operation)
end of pipeline. 
automatic iteration internal iteration


java.util.stream;

Stream creation-> collection Arrays.stream(arr[])
Stream<String> stream = Arrays.stream(new String{"31","21","21"});
stream = Stream.of("31","21","21");

.stream() is method available in Collection interface which allows 
conversion of collection to stream type

Stream<String> stream = list.stream();

Once stream is consumed it cant be reused
